Hello! Hello out there :) it is March Meet The Maker time & I'm jumping in this year... in an effort to be more open.

Today is Brand Origin. I have a hybrid type brand & am excited to share a bit about it.

>>>The first part is @UmWowStudio - my product design based business for mixed media art supplies. It's all the stuff i myself love to use. It's a mix of new artist designed & manufactured products + my love of using & sourcing amazing vintage items. 

The name comes from a pack of friends brainstorming session in college. Incidentally, that's where i also gained the basis for my product design abilities. I have a Bachelor of Arts degree in Industrial Design. 

>>>The second part of my brand is @DeeDeeCatron - my name, my self & my artistic abilities. I make art. I experiment in art. I hone my raw art brain. I teach art & I rely heavily on products I've designed myself because they match my artistic needs & wants.

It's truly a lovely mix of all the things I want... to be immersed in art.

It's edgy, badass, innovative, experimentational, creative, graphic, vintage & grungy & oh so inspirational. It's MY brand. It's unapologetically DeeDee. 

Feel free to ask me anything you want about my brand & if i'm comfortable i'll answer!

Hello HELLO! this is ME - #marchmeetthemaker2023 day 2 is All About You - so let me spill some deets ♡

>i am 35. I have a bachelor of arts degree in industrial design & I have been some form of artist or maker my whole life. 

>Business & creativity are my jam. I find it so interesting to learn about how people make money, especially creatives! We are truly an innovative & miraculous species that always keeps me on my toes. 

>i am (almost) 13 years married to the love of my life. We have a 12 year old human boy, a 13 year old dachshund boy, & a 1 year old german shepherd heeler girl. 

>i am the sole body at @umwowstudio. I design, make, produce, gather, package, ship, store, sort, hr, customer service, fund and any & all other parts of UWS. 

>i am continually a work in progress.

>i friggin' LOVE vintage items & antiques.

>i love working with other creatives & introducing new exciting ideas to the world! - like #inDExed kit with @adogslife13 & @theuglyartclub with @alteredstatesstudio & @southerngals_designs. 

>i am drawn to old papers, bold black & white marks, & fibery bits.

>i want to be unapologetic in who i am without being cruel or unkind. i want to support my friends & encourage all creatives to take the next step. i want to champion for the planet.

>i also really love all things celestial & otherworldly

Closure real talk : i get a little anxious when it comes to choosing the bit that will secure my books closed. I love buttons, snaps, wraps, bundlee, ties, clips... all the things. 

For my #janechippzoom book, i decided to use a hybrid button wrap... i KNOW this book will get fat, so i can make these longer if need be. I can also alter 'em to high hell! & they aren't tied down = winning

I opted for the cotton ribbon & wood buttons via @umwowstudio. They fit right in with these aged vintage neutrals. 

Happy sigh
